    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-03T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-03T01:00:00-05:00" n="832"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11423: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-03T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 3, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 3—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1074. At about 1 o’clock today when the Japanese forces were carrying out their
                    ill-advised military parade through the Settlement a hand grenade was thrown by
                    a Chinese on Nanking Road. It is reported that one Japanese soldier, one
                    Japanese civilian and two <pb facs="0757" n="750" xml:id="pg_750"/> Shanghai
                    municipal policemen were wounded and that the thrower of the hand grenade was
                    shot and killed by the police. The parade continued and has now cleared Nanking
                    Road and the Bund.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Tokyo, Nanking, Hankow, and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
